cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for relation extraction in biomedical text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel model architecture that uses self-attention and bi-affine operations, which are common techniques in deep learning and neural networks, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of multi-instance learning, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
